ce:section.ce:para:
The specific steps are as follows:

                              (1)

Define the neighborhood radius ε and the density threshold MinPts;


                              (2)

Arbitrarily select an unvisited point k, count the number n of points within a distance less than ε from it (including the point itself), if n≥MinPts, then point k is a core point; create a new cluster V, place the points within its neighborhood radius ε into the cluster V, and mark them as visited;


                              (3)

Traverse the points in the neighborhood of k, if there is a point b in the neighborhood that is a core point, then include the points in the neighborhood of b into cluster V, and so on, until V no longer expands;


                              (4)

Repeat steps 2 and 3 until all points have been visited.
